This paper is about image super-resolution, which is a topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a novel Style-based Super-Resolution Variational Autoencoder network (SSRVAE) that contains a style Variational Autoencoder (styleVAE) and a SR Network. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of mutual information estimation (MI), which is a technique commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) research.
